
1.2.1
 - Room and user names can no longer contain a / character - [Dreamer]
 - 'reply .feeling argument' was causing a crash - [Dreamer]
 - Fixed bug where a user could seem to be disconnected twice in succession.
 - Closing user sockets are now disconnected before select() is called as
   well as after.
 - Previously, if ^C was pressed at the password prompt of a console mode
   talker, echo would remain off in the running shell - [Neil.R]

1.2.2
 - If a user with no password set went auto-afk, the talker would crash when
   that user next typed anything.

